messages.content:
When a parent process exits before its children, those children become orphans and must be reparented. The implementation is in `kernel/exit.c`.

**forget_original_parent()**: Called during `do_exit()` for the dying process:
```c
static void forget_original_parent(struct task_struct *father, 
                                    struct list_head *dead) {
    struct task_struct *p, *reaper;
    reaper = find_alive_thread(father);  // try thread in same thread group
    if (!reaper)
        reaper = task_child_reaper(father);  // PID namespace init (PID 1)

    list_for_each_entry(p, &father->children, sibling) {
        p->real_parent = reaper;
        BUG_ON(p->parent == p->real_parent);  // parent may differ due to ptrace
        if (p->pdeath_signal)
            group_send_sig_info(p->pdeath_signal, SEND_SIG_NOINFO, p, PIDTYPE_PID);
    }
}
```

**Reparenting priority**:
1. First, look for another thread in the same thread group (`find_alive_thread()`). This keeps children within the same process.
2. If no suitable thread exists, use the PID namespace's child_reaper (typically PID 1, the init process in that namespace).

**PR_SET_PDEATHSIG**: Children that set a parent death signal via `prctl(PR_SET_PDEATHSIG)` receive that signal when the parent dies. This is checked during reparenting.

**Stopped orphan handling**: POSIX requires that if an orphan process group has any stopped members, all members receive SIGHUP followed by SIGCONT. This is handled in `kill_orphaned_pgrp()`:
```c
static void kill_orphaned_pgrp(struct task_struct *tsk, 
                                struct task_struct *parent) {
    struct pid *pgrp = task_pgrp(tsk);
    if (!will_become_orphaned_pgrp(pgrp, tsk))
        return;
    // Send SIGHUP then SIGCONT to the process group
    do_each_pid_task(pgrp, PIDTYPE_PGID, p) {
        group_send_sig_info(SIGHUP, SEND_SIG_PRIV, p, PIDTYPE_PGID);
        group_send_sig_info(SIGCONT, SEND_SIG_PRIV, p, PIDTYPE_PGID);
    }
}
```

**Zombie children**: If the dying parent has zombie children, they are reparented to the new parent (the reaper). The reaper's `SIGCHLD` handler (or implicit reaping for init) will eventually collect their exit status via `wait()`.

**Init process role**: PID 1 has a special signal disposition for SIGCHLD — it automatically reaps zombie children. This is implemented via `SA_NOCLDWAIT` behavior in `wait_consider_task()` when the parent is init.

The per-CPU pageset (PCP) tracks page 'temperature' to optimize cache and TLB usage. Hot pages were recently freed and likely have useful cache/TLB entries. Cold pages have been free longer.

**Implementation:**
Pages on the per-CPU lists are ordered by temperature. Recently freed pages are added to the 'hot' end (head of list), while allocation takes from the 'hot' end. Pages that remain on the list become 'cold' as they age toward the tail.

```c
// Allocation: take from head (hot pages)
static struct page *__rmqueue_pcplist(struct zone *zone, unsigned int order,
                                       int migratetype,
                                       struct per_cpu_pages *pcp)
{
    struct page *page;
    page = list_first_entry(&pcp->lists[migratetype], struct page, lru);
    list_del(&page->lru);
    pcp->count -= 1 << order;
    return page;
}

// Free: add to head (make it hot)
static void free_one_page_to_pcplist(struct page *page,
                                       struct per_cpu_pages *pcp,
                                       int migratetype)
{
    list_add(&page->lru, &pcp->lists[migratetype]);
    pcp->count++;
}
```

**Why temperature matters:**
- Hot pages likely have their data still in CPU cache (L1/L2/L3)
- Hot pages may have TLB entries that are still valid
- Allocating hot pages improves cache hit rate
- Cold pages may have stale cache lines, reducing performance

**Cache coloring interaction:**
The PCP lists are per-migration-type, which provides a form of cache coloring. Pages freed by one type of workload tend to be reused by the same type, maintaining cache locality.

**Drain mechanism:**
When PCP lists exceed the high watermark, pages are drained back to the buddy allocator:
```c
static void drain_pages_zone(unsigned long cpu, struct zone *zone)
{
    struct per_cpu_pages *pcp = per_cpu_ptr(zone->pageset, cpu);

    // Move all PCP pages to buddy free lists
    while (!list_empty(&pcp->lists[migratetype])) {
        page = list_first_entry(...);
        __free_one_page(page, zone, 0, migratetype);
    }
}
```

Draining is triggered by: memory pressure, memory hotplug, hibernation, and explicit drain calls.

CONFIG_HARDENED_USERCOPY adds bounds checking to copy_to/from_user(). Verifies kernel buffer is within expected bounds: valid slab object, copy size doesn't exceed object size, doesn't cross object boundaries. Catches corrupted length/pointer bugs. ~1-2% overhead. Introduced kernel 4.8. Example of a basic character device driver skeleton:
```c
#include <linux/module.h>
#include <linux/fs.h>
#include <linux/cdev.h>
#include <linux/device.h>

static int major;
static struct class *cls;

static ssize_t mydev_read(struct file *f, char __user *buf,
                          size_t count, loff_t *ppos)
{
    char msg[] = "Hello from kernel!\n";
    return simple_read_from_buffer(buf, count, ppos, msg, strlen(msg));
}

static struct file_operations fops = {
    .owner = THIS_MODULE,
    .read = mydev_read,
};

static int __init mydev_init(void)
{
    major = register_chrdev(0, "mydev", &fops);
    cls = class_create(THIS_MODULE, "mydev");
    device_create(cls, NULL, MKDEV(major, 0), NULL, "mydev");
    return 0;
}

static void __exit mydev_exit(void)
{
    device_destroy(cls, MKDEV(major, 0));
    class_destroy(cls);
    unregister_chrdev(major, "mydev");
}

module_init(mydev_init);
module_exit(mydev_exit);
MODULE_LICENSE("GPL");
```

```c
#include <linux/slab.h>
#include <linux/string.h>

struct device_info {
    int id;
    char *name;
    u32 *data;
    size_t data_len;
};

static struct device_info *create_device(int id, const char *name,
                                         size_t data_count)
{
    struct device_info *dev;
    size_t name_len;

    /*
     * CORRECT: kzalloc zeroes memory, preventing info leaks
     * and ensuring pointers are NULL (safe for kfree on error)
     */
    dev = kzalloc(sizeof(*dev), GFP_KERNEL);
    if (!dev)
        return NULL;

    dev->id = id;

    /*
     * CORRECT: kstrdup allocates and copies in one call
     * WRONG: manually kmalloc + strcpy (error-prone)
     */
    dev->name = kstrdup(name, GFP_KERNEL);
    if (!dev->name)
        goto err_name;

    /*
     * CORRECT: kcalloc checks for multiplication overflow
     * WRONG: kmalloc(data_count * sizeof(u32), GFP_KERNEL)
     *   - No overflow check! data_count * sizeof(u32) can
     *     overflow on 32-bit systems
     */
    dev->data = kcalloc(data_count, sizeof(u32), GFP_KERNEL);
    if (!dev->data)
        goto err_data;

    dev->data_len = data_count;
    return dev;

err_data:
    kfree(dev->name);  /* kfree(NULL) is safe */
err_name:
    kfree(dev);
    return NULL;
}

static void destroy_device(struct device_info *dev)
{
    if (!dev)
        return;
    kfree(dev->data);
    kfree(dev->name);
    kfree(dev);
}
```
常见错误：(1) 使用kmalloc替代kcalloc导致整数溢出；(2) 忘记检查kstrdup返回值；(3) 错误路径中忘记释放已分配的资源；(4) 对kfree(NULL)的担忧——kfree(NULL)是安全的no-op。

`mremap()`（系统调用号25，x86_64）用于调整已有内存映射的大小，可以扩展或收缩映射区域，甚至将其移动到新的虚拟地址。这是Linux特有的系统调用。

**系统调用接口**：
```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE5(mremap, unsigned long, addr, unsigned long, old_len,
    unsigned long, new_len, unsigned long, flags, unsigned long, new_addr) {
    return do_mremap(addr, old_len, new_len, flags, new_addr);
}
```

**标志**：
- `MREMAP_MAYMOVE` (1)：允许内核将映射移动到新地址
- `MREMAP_FIXED` (2)：指定新地址（必须与MREMAP_MAYMOVE一起使用）
- `MREMAP_DONTUNMAP` (4)：不移除旧映射（Linux 5.7+）

**扩展映射**：
当扩展时，内核检查映射后面是否有空闲的虚拟地址空间：
```c
// mm/mremap.c
static unsigned long mremap_to(unsigned long addr, unsigned long old_len,
                                unsigned long new_addr, unsigned long new_len) {
    // 1. 尝试原地扩展（不需要移动）
    vma = vma_lookup(mm, addr);
    if (vma->vm_end - addr >= new_len) {
        // 映射后面有足够空间
        do_vma_munmap(vma, addr + old_len, old_len - new_len);
        vma_adjust(vma, addr, addr + new_len, ...);
        return addr;  // 原地扩展成功
    }

    // 2. 需要移动（MREMAP_MAYMOVE）
    new_vma = copy_vma(&vma, new_addr, new_len, ...);
    move_page_tables(vma, addr, new_vma, new_addr, old_len);
    do_munmap(mm, addr, old_len);  // 移除旧映射
    return new_addr;
}
```

**页表移动**：
```c
static void move_page_tables(struct vm_area_struct *vma, unsigned long old_addr,
                              struct vm_area_struct *new_vma, unsigned long new_addr,
                              unsigned long len) {
    // 逐个PMD/PTE级别移动页表项
    for (; old_addr < old_end; old_addr += PMD_SIZE, new_addr += PMD_SIZE) {
        // 尝试移动整个PMD（大页优化）
        if (move_pgt_entry(NORMAL_ENTRY, vma, old_addr, new_addr, ...))
            continue;
        // 否则逐个PTE移动
        move_ptes(vma, old_pmd, old_addr, new_addr, ...);
    }
    flush_tlb_range(vma, old_addr, old_addr + len);
}
```

**使用场景**：
1. **动态数组调整**：替代 `malloc/realloc` 中需要调整 mmap 区域大小的场景
2. **JIT编译器**：扩展代码缓冲区而不复制
3. **glibc malloc**：使用 `mremap()` 扩展主堆区域
4. **数据库缓冲区池**：动态调整共享内存段大小

**与mmap+munmap对比**：
- `mremap()` 保持页面内容，只是移动页表项
- `mmap()` 新地址 + `memcpy()` + `munmap()` 旧地址会产生物理页面复制
- `mremap()` 更快，因为它只移动页表项而不移动物理页面

模块通知器链广播模块状态更改给已注册监听器。事件：MODULE_STATE_COMING（加载中）、MODULE_STATE_LIVE（已加载）、MODULE_STATE_GOING（卸载中）。监听器包括：livepatch、ftrace、kprobes、cfi、lockdep。通过register_module_notifier()注册。 Example of using RCU for safe linked list traversal:
```c
struct my_entry {
    int value;
    struct list_head list;
    struct rcu_head rcu;
};

/* Reader - no lock needed */
void reader(void)
{
    struct my_entry *entry;
    rcu_read_lock();
    list_for_each_entry_rcu(entry, &my_list, list) {
        if (entry->value == target)
            do_something(entry);
    }
    rcu_read_unlock();
}

/* Writer - must hold lock */
void writer(struct my_entry *old, struct my_entry *new)
{
    spin_lock(&my_lock);
    list_replace_rcu(&old->list, &new->list);
    spin_unlock(&my_lock);
    kfree_rcu(old, rcu);  /* Free after grace period */
}
```

`rt_sigreturn()`是Linux内核中信号处理机制的关键组成部分，它负责在信号处理函数执行完毕后恢复被中断程序的执行上下文。这个过程涉及复杂的用户栈操作和内核态/用户态的协调。

**信号投递过程**：

当内核需要将一个信号投递给进程时（在`do_signal()`中），它会执行以下步骤：

1. **选择信号帧位置**：
   - 默认使用用户栈（向下增长）
   - 如果设置了`SA_ONSTACK`标志且通过`sigaltstack()`注册了备用栈，则使用备用信号栈
   - 栈地址向下对齐到8字节（或16字节，取决于ABI）

2. **构建信号帧**（在`setup_rt_frame()`中）：
   ```c
   struct rt_sigframe {
       char __user *pretcode;        // 伪返回地址（指向sigreturn trampoline）
       struct siginfo info;          // 信号详细信息
       struct ucontext uc;           // 完整的用户上下文
       // ucontext包含：
       //   - ucontext.uc_sigmask: 信号掩码
       //   - ucontext.uc_mcontext: 寄存器状态（gregset_t）
       //   - ucontext.uc_stack: 栈信息
       //   - fpstate: FPU/SSE/AVX寄存器状态
   };
   ```

3. **保存寄存器状态**：
   ```c
   // arch/x86/kernel/signal.c
   static int x86_setup_sigcontext(struct sigcontext __user *sc, struct pt_regs *regs) {
       // 保存所有通用寄存器
       put_user(regs->di, &sc->di);
       put_user(regs->si, &sc->si);
       put_user(regs->bp, &sc->bp);
       put_user(regs->sp, &sc->sp);
       put_user(regs->bx, &sc->bx);
       put_user(regs->dx, &sc->dx);
       put_user(regs->cx, &sc->cx);
       put_user(regs->ax, &sc->ax);
       put_user(regs->ip, &sc->ip);
       put_user(regs->flags, &sc->flags);
       // 保存段寄存器
   }
   ```

4. **设置FPU/SSE状态**：
   - `copy_fpregs_to_sigframe()`保存x87 FPU、SSE和AVX寄存器到信号帧
   - 这对于保证浮点计算的连续性至关重要

5. **设置返回地址**：
   - 在信号帧的"返回地址"位置写入VDSO中`__kernel_rt_sigreturn`的地址
   - 这个trampoline执行`mov $__NR_rt_sigreturn, %eax; syscall`

6. **修改pt_regs**：
   ```c
   regs->sp = (unsigned long)frame;     // 栈指向信号帧
   regs->ip = (unsigned long)handler;   // 指令指针指向信号处理函数
   regs->ax = sig;                       // 第一个参数：信号编号
   regs->di = sig;                       // System V ABI: RDI = 第一个参数
   regs->si = (unsigned long)&frame->info;  // 第二个参数
   regs->dx = (unsigned long)&frame->uc;    // 第三个参数
   ```

**rt_sigreturn()实现**：

当信号处理函数返回时，执行`__kernel_rt_sigreturn` trampoline，触发`rt_sigreturn`系统调用（编号15）：

```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE0(rt_sigreturn) {
    struct pt_regs *regs = task_pt_regs(current);
    struct rt_sigframe __user *frame;
    sigset_t set;

    frame = (struct rt_sigframe __user *)(regs->sp);

    // 验证信号帧地址
    if (!access_ok(frame, sizeof(*frame)))
        goto badframe;

    // 恢复信号掩码
    if (copy_from_user(&set, &frame->uc.uc_sigmask, sizeof(set)))
        goto badframe;
    set_current_blocked(&set);

    // 恢复寄存器状态
    if (restore_sigcontext(regs, &frame->uc.uc_mcontext))
        goto badframe;

    // 恢复FPU状态
    if (restore_altstack(&frame->uc.uc_stack))
        goto badframe;

    return regs->ax;  // 恢复的返回值
}
```

**安全验证**：
- `restore_sigcontext()`会验证恢复的RIP和RSP值是否在用户空间范围内
- CS和SS段寄存器必须匹配用户态值
- RFLAGS中的危险位（如IF-中断标志）被过滤
- 防止恶意构造的信号帧将执行跳转到内核空间

**与sigreturn的区别**：`rt_sigreturn`支持`siginfo_t`和更大的信号集（64位），而旧的`sigreturn`只支持32位信号集。现代Linux统一使用`rt_sigreturn`。

以下eBPF程序根据系统负载动态调整采样率：

```c
#include "vmlinux.h"
#include <bpf/bpf_helpers.h>
#include <bpf/bpf_tracing.h>

struct {
    __uint(type, BPF_MAP_TYPE_ARRAY);
    __uint(max_entries, 1);
    __type(key, __u32);
    __type(value, __u64);
} event_count SEC(".maps");

struct {
    __uint(type, BPF_MAP_TYPE_ARRAY);
    __uint(max_entries, 1);
    __type(key, __u32);
    __type(value, __u32);
} sample_rate SEC(".maps");  // 采样率：每N个事件采样一次

struct {
    __uint(type, BPF_MAP_TYPE_RINGBUF);
    __uint(max_entries, 256 * 1024);
} events SEC(".maps");

SEC("kprobe/tcp_sendmsg")
int trace_send(struct pt_regs *ctx) {
    __u32 key = 0;
    __u64 *count = bpf_map_lookup_elem(&event_count, &key);
    __u32 *rate = bpf_map_lookup_elem(&sample_rate, &key);
    if (!count || !rate || *rate == 0) return 0;

    __sync_fetch_and_add(count, 1);

    // 自适应采样
    if (*count % *rate != 0) return 0;

    // 每10秒调整采样率（用户空间实现）
    struct {
        __u64 timestamp;
        __u32 pid;
        __u64 bytes;
    } *e;
    e = bpf_ringbuf_reserve(&events, sizeof(*e), 0);
    if (!e) return 0;
    e->timestamp = bpf_ktime_get_ns();
    e->pid = bpf_get_current_pid_tgid() >> 32;
    e->bytes = PT_REGS_PARM3(ctx);
    bpf_ringbuf_submit(e, 0);
    return 0;
}

char LICENSE[] SEC("license") = "GPL";
```

用户空间程序每10秒读取event_count，如果事件数过高（>10000），增大sample_rate降低采样频率；如果事件数过低（<100），减小sample_rate提高采样频率。这种自适应策略在保持统计精度的同时控制了BPF程序的开销。

实现动态大小的无锁哈希表需要结合RCU、原子操作和延迟释放。

```c
#include <linux/rcupdate.h>
#include <linux/slab.h>

struct ht_entry {
    unsigned long key;
    void *value;
    struct hlist_node node;
    struct rcu_head rcu;
};

struct ht_bucket {
    spinlock_t lock;
    struct hlist_head head;
};

struct dyn_htable {
    struct ht_bucket __rcu *buckets;
    unsigned int size;          /* 当前大小（2的幂）*/
    unsigned int count;
    struct mutex resize_lock;   /* 序列化resize操作 */
};

/* 无锁查找 */
void *ht_lookup(struct dyn_htable *ht, unsigned long key) {
    struct ht_bucket *buckets;
    struct ht_entry *e;
    unsigned int idx;
    void *result = NULL;

    rcu_read_lock();
    buckets = rcu_dereference(ht->buckets);
    idx = hash_long(key, ilog2(ht->size));
    hlist_for_each_entry_rcu(e, &buckets[idx].head, node) {
        if (e->key == key) {
            result = e->value;
            break;
        }
    }
    rcu_read_unlock();
    return result;
}

/* 插入 */
int ht_insert(struct dyn_htable *ht, unsigned long key, void *value) {
    struct ht_entry *e = kmalloc(sizeof(*e), GFP_KERNEL);
    struct ht_bucket *buckets;
    unsigned int idx;

    e->key = key; e->value = value;
    rcu_read_lock();
    buckets = rcu_dereference(ht->buckets);
    idx = hash_long(key, ilog2(ht->size));
    spin_lock(&buckets[idx].lock);
    hlist_add_head_rcu(&e->node, &buckets[idx].head);
    spin_unlock(&buckets[idx].lock);
    rcu_read_unlock();
    return 0;
}

/* 动态扩容 */
int ht_resize(struct dyn_htable *ht, unsigned int new_size) {
    struct ht_bucket *old_buckets, *new_buckets;
    unsigned int i, old_size;

    new_buckets = kcalloc(new_size, sizeof(*new_buckets), GFP_KERNEL);
    for (i = 0; i < new_size; i++)
        spin_lock_init(&new_buckets[i].lock);

    mutex_lock(&ht->resize_lock);
    old_buckets = ht->buckets;
    old_size = ht->size;

    /* 重新哈希所有条目到新桶 */
    for (i = 0; i < old_size; i++) {
        struct ht_entry *e;
        spin_lock(&old_buckets[i].lock);
        hlist_for_each_entry(e, &old_buckets[i].head, node) {
            unsigned int new_idx = hash_long(e->key, ilog2(new_size));
            hlist_add_head(&e->node, &new_buckets[new_idx].head);
        }
        spin_unlock(&old_buckets[i].lock);
    }

    /* 原子替换指针 */
    rcu_assign_pointer(ht->buckets, new_buckets);
    ht->size = new_size;
    mutex_unlock(&ht->resize_lock);

    /* 等待所有读者完成后释放旧桶 */
    synchronize_rcu();
    kfree(old_buckets);
    return 0;
}
```

核心设计：(1)RCU保护读路径。(2)per-bucket spinlock保护写操作。(3)resize使用mutex序列化。(4)synchronize_rcu后释放旧数据。(5)实际内核使用rhashtable。

```c
struct inode *ext4_iget(struct super_block *sb, unsigned long ino) {
    inode = iget_locked(sb, ino);
    if (!(inode->i_state & I_NEW)) return inode;
    ext4_get_inode_loc(inode, &iloc); // compute disk location
    raw_inode = ext4_raw_inode(&iloc);
    inode->i_mode = le16_to_cpu(raw_inode->i_mode);
    inode->i_size = le32_to_cpu(raw_inode->i_size_lo);
    // Set i_op/i_fop based on S_ISREG/S_ISDIR/S_ISLNK
    unlock_new_inode(inode);
}
```
On cache miss, reads block group inode table via sb_bread(), translates from little-endian.

The inode abstraction is fundamental to Unix filesystem design. The principle of 'everything is a file' is realized through inodes: regular files, directories, device nodes, pipes, sockets, and symlinks are all represented by inodes with different `i_mode` types. The inode number (`i_ino`) provides a unique identifier within a filesystem, enabling hard links (multiple directory entries pointing to the same inode) and efficient file identification. The `stat()` system call returns inode metadata without opening the file, enabling tools like `find`, `ls`, and `du` to operate efficiently on large directory trees. The kernel maintains several caches for inodes: the inode hash table for fast lookup by number, the inode LRU for memory management, and the per-superblock dirty list for writeback coordination.

The inode cache management involves several interacting subsystems. The inode hash table provides O(1) lookup by inode number within a superblock. The LRU list tracks unused inodes for memory reclamation. The dirty list coordinates writeback timing. The slab allocator provides fast allocation with cache-line alignment. When memory pressure occurs, the inode shrinker evicts unused inodes from the LRU, first writing back any dirty metadata via `write_inode()`. The `iput()` function handles the complex lifecycle: decrementing the reference count, checking for deletion (nlink==0), and coordinating with the shrinker. RCU-deferred freeing ensures that concurrent RCU readers accessing the inode complete before memory is reused.

MAP_HUGETLB requests the kernel to back the mapping with explicit huge pages from the hugetlbfs pool, rather than regular 4KB pages or transparent huge pages.

**mmap with MAP_HUGETLB:**
```c
// Request 2MB huge page mapping
void *addr = mmap(NULL, size, PROT_READ|PROT_WRITE,
                  MAP_PRIVATE | MAP_ANONYMOUS | MAP_HUGETLB, -1, 0);
```

**Implementation path:**
1. do_mmap() detects MAP_HUGETLB and calls hugetlb_file_setup():
```c
static unsigned long do_mmap(struct file *file, unsigned long addr, ...)
{
    if (flags & MAP_HUGETLB) {
        // Create an anonymous hugetlb file
        file = hugetlb_file_setup("", size, VM_NORESERVE,
                                  &user, HUGETLB_ANONHUGE_INODE,
                                  hstate_sizelog(flags >> MAP_HUGE_SHIFT));
    }
}
```

2. The hugetlb file's vm_ops provides a special fault handler:
```c
static const struct vm_operations_struct hugetlb_vm_ops = {
    .fault = hugetlb_fault,
    .open = hugetlb_vm_open,
    .close = hugetlb_vm_close,
};
```

3. hugetlb_fault() allocates from the huge page pool:
```c
static vm_fault_t hugetlb_fault(struct mm_struct *mm, struct vm_area_struct *vma,
                                 unsigned long address, unsigned int flags)
{
    // Get the huge page state for this mapping
    struct hstate *h = hstate_vma(vma);

    // Try to allocate a huge page from the pool
    page = alloc_huge_page(vma, address, ...);
    if (IS_ERR(page)) {
        if (PTR_ERR(page) == -ENOSPC)
            return VM_FAULT_OOM;   // No huge pages available
        return VM_FAULT_SIGBUS;
    }

    // Set up the huge PTE (PMD-level for 2MB)
    huge_ptep = huge_pte_alloc(mm, vma, address, huge_page_size(h));
    set_huge_pte_at(mm, address, huge_ptep, make_huge_pte(vma, page, ...));
}
```

**Huge page pool management:**
```bash
# Allocate huge pages at runtime
echo 1024 > /proc/sys/vm/nr_hugepages      # 1024 x 2MB = 2GB
echo 4 > /sys/kernel/mm/hugepages/hugepages-1048576kB/nr_hugepages  # 4 x 1GB

# Per-node allocation
echo 512 > /sys/devices/system/node/node0/hugepages/hugepages-2048kB/nr_hugepages
```

**MAP_HUGETLB vs MAP_ANONYMOUS with THP:**
| Aspect | MAP_HUGETLB | THP (MAP_ANONYMOUS) |
|--------|------------|---------------------|
| Page source | Pre-allocated pool | Buddy allocator |
| Guarantee | Yes (if pool not empty) | Best-effort |
| Page sizes | 2MB, 1GB (configurable) | 2MB only |
| Split | Never | Can split |
| Overcommit | No (reserved pool) | Yes |

function_graph是ftrace中最强大的追踪器之一，它不仅记录函数调用，还追踪函数的返回，以缩进的调用图形式展示完整的执行路径和每个函数的耗时。这对于理解复杂的内核代码流程特别有价值。

使用function_graph非常简单。首先选择追踪器：echo function_graph > /sys/kernel/tracing/current_tracer。然后启用追踪：echo 1 > /sys/kernel/tracing/tracing_on。读取结果：cat /sys/kernel/tracing/trace。输出格式类似C代码的调用关系，每个函数调用有对应的开括号{和闭括号}，函数名前用|表示缩进层级，每行末尾显示该函数的执行时间。

输出中函数名后的数字表示执行耗时：如果函数在100微秒内完成，显示正常时间；超过100微秒显示加号(+)；超过1000微秒显示感叹号(!)。这可以快速识别慢路径。例如：
  schedule() {
    12.345 us    pick_next_task();
    2.100 us    context_switch();
  }

为了避免输出过多数据，通常配合过滤器使用。set_graph_function限制只追踪特定函数及其子调用：echo tcp_sendmsg > set_graph_function。set_graph_notrace排除不感兴趣的函数。max_graph_depth限制追踪深度，例如echo 3 > max_graph_depth只追踪3层调用。

function_graph的开销比function追踪器大，因为它需要在函数返回时也进行记录。在高频率调用的函数上使用可能导致明显性能下降。建议在开发或问题排查时使用，而非长期在生产环境启用。

`process_vm_readv()` and `process_vm_writev()` (syscall numbers 310 and 311 on x86_64) allow efficient cross-process memory transfer using scatter-gather I/O, without the overhead of ptrace.

**System Call Interface**:
```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE6(process_vm_readv, pid_t, pid,
    const struct iovec __user *, lvec, unsigned long, liovcnt,
    const struct iovec __user *, rvec, unsigned long, riovcnt,
    unsigned long, flags) {
    return process_vm_rw_core(pid, lvec, liovcnt, rvec, riovcnt, 0, 0);
}
```

**How It Works**: `process_vm_readv()` copies data from a remote process's address space into the caller's local buffers. It uses the iovec (scatter-gather) model:

```c
// Read from remote process
struct iovec local[] = {
    { .iov_base = local_buf1, .iov_len = 100 },
    { .iov_base = local_buf2, .iov_len = 200 },
};
struct iovec remote[] = {
    { .iov_base = (void *)0x7f1234000000, .iov_len = 100 },
    { .iov_base = (void *)0x7f1234001000, .iov_len = 200 },
};
ssize_t ret = process_vm_readv(target_pid, local, 2, remote, 2, 0);
```

**Internal Implementation**:
```c
static ssize_t process_vm_rw_core(pid_t pid, struct iov_iter *iter,
                                   struct iovec *rvec, unsigned long riovcnt,
                                   unsigned long flags, bool vm_read) {
    struct task_struct *task;
    struct mm_struct *mm;

    // Find the target process
    task = find_get_task_by_vpid(pid);
    mm = mm_access(task, PTRACE_MODE_ATTACH_REALCREDS);

    // For each remote iovec
    for (i = 0; i < riovcnt; i++) {
        // Pin remote pages and copy data
        nr_pages = process_vm_rw_single_vec(mm, rvec[i].iov_base,
                                             rvec[i].iov_len,
                                             &cur_iov, vm_read);
    }

    mmput(mm);
    put_task_struct(task);
}
```

**process_vm_rw_single_vec()**: Uses `get_user_pages_remote()` to pin the target process's pages:
1. Resolves virtual addresses in the target's page tables
2. Pins pages in memory (prevents swapping)
3. Uses `kmap()` to get kernel-accessible addresses
4. Copies data between local and remote buffers

**Advantages Over ptrace**:
- **No process stop required**: `process_vm_readv()` works on running processes without sending SIGSTOP
- **Bulk transfer**: Scatter-gather allows reading multiple regions in a single syscall
- **Better performance**: No ptrace attach/detach overhead, no signal delivery
- **Thread-safe**: Can read from specific threads without affecting the whole process

**Permission Check**: Requires `CAP_SYS_PTRACE` or the same UID as the target process. YAMA `ptrace_scope` also applies.

**Use Cases**:
1. **Debugging**: Reading remote process state without stopping it
2. **Monitoring**: Tools like `htop` reading `/proc/<pid>` data
3. **HPC**: MPI implementations transferring data between processes on the same node
4. **CRIU** (Checkpoint/Restore): Saving and restoring process memory images

**Error Cases**:
- `-ESRCH`: Target process not found
- `-EFAULT`: Remote address not mapped in target process
- `-EPERM`: Insufficient permissions
- `-EINVAL`: Invalid flags or iovec parameters

抢占（preemption）和调度（scheduling）在Linux内核中紧密关联。

**抢占的基本流程**：
```c
/* 1. preempt_disable: 禁止抢占 */
preempt_disable();  /* preempt_count++ */
/* 此代码区域内不会被调度器抢占 */
critical_section();
preempt_enable();   /* preempt_count--, 检查TIF_NEED_RESCHED */

/* 2. preempt_enable触发调度检查 */
static inline void preempt_enable(void) {
    barrier();
    if (unlikely(preempt_count_dec_and_test())) {
        /* preempt_count达到0 */
        if (need_resched())  /* TIF_NEED_RESCHED被设置 */
            __preempt_schedule();  /* 调用调度器 */
    }
}
```

**TIF_NEED_RESCHED标志**：
```c
/* 设置时机：*/
/* - 更高优先级任务变为可运行 */
/* - 当前任务时间片用完 */
/* - 显式调用set_tsk_need_resched() */

/* 检查时机：*/
/* - preempt_enable() */
/* - 从系统调用/中断返回用户空间 */
/* - cond_resched()显式调用 */
```

**cond_resched()**：
```c
/* 在长循环中主动让出CPU */
while (processing_large_data()) {
    process_chunk();
    cond_resched();  /* 如果需要调度，让出CPU */
}
```

**锁与抢占的关系**：spin_lock内部禁用抢占，持有spinlock时不会被调度。mutex_lock可能导致调度（任务睡眠）。这就是为什么不能在持有spinlock时调用可能睡眠的函数。

`irq_default_primary_handler()` is a minimal hardirq handler that simply returns `IRQ_WAKE_THREAD`. It is used as the hardirq handler when `request_threaded_irq()` is called with a NULL hardirq handler and `IRQF_ONESHOT`. Its implementation is trivial:
```c
static irqreturn_t irq_default_primary_handler(int irq, void *dev_id)
{
    return IRQ_WAKE_THREAD;
}
```
This handler exists because `request_threaded_irq()` requires a non-NULL hardirq handler (the IRQ core needs something to run in hardirq context to acknowledge the interrupt and decide whether to wake the thread). When all processing is done in the threaded handler (common for I2C/SPI devices), this default handler provides the minimal bridge. With `CONFIG_IRQ_FORCED_THREADING`, this handler replaces the original handler when forced threading is active.

`getrlimit()`和`setrlimit()`系统调用（编号97和160，x86_64）用于查询和设置进程的资源限制。这些限制由内核强制执行，防止单个进程消耗过多系统资源。

**系统调用接口**：
```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE2(getrlimit, unsigned int, resource, 
    struct rlimit __user *, rlim) {
    struct rlimit value;
    task_rlimit(current, resource, &value);
    if (copy_to_user(rlim, &value, sizeof(value)))
        return -EFAULT;
    return 0;
}

SYSCALL_DEFINE2(setrlimit, unsigned int, resource, 
    struct rlimit __user *, rlim) {
    struct rlimit new_rlim;
    if (copy_from_user(&new_rlim, rlim, sizeof(new_rlim)))
        return -EFAULT;
    return do_setrlimit(resource, &new_rlim, 0);
}
```

**rlimit结构**：
```c
struct rlimit {
    unsigned long rlim_cur;  // 软限制（soft limit）
    unsigned long rlim_max;  // 硬限制（hard limit）
};
```

**软限制与硬限制**：
- **软限制（rlim_cur）**：内核实际强制执行的限制值
- **硬限制（rlim_max）**：软限制的上限。非特权进程只能降低硬限制，不能提高
- 特权进程（具有`CAP_SYS_RESOURCE`）可以提高硬限制

**重要资源限制**：

1. **RLIMIT_AS** (9)：虚拟地址空间大小上限。超过后`mmap()`和`brk()`返回`-ENOMEM`。

2. **RLIMIT_CORE** (4)：核心转储文件的最大大小。设为0禁用核心转储。

3. **RLIMIT_CPU** (0)：CPU时间限制（秒）。超过软限制时发送`SIGXCPU`，超过硬限制时发送`SIGKILL`。

4. **RLIMIT_DATA** (2)：数据段大小上限（`brk()`和`mmap()`匿名映射）。

5. **RLIMIT_FSIZE** (1)：文件大小上限。超过时发送`SIGXFSZ`并返回`-EFBIG`。

6. **RLIMIT_MEMLOCK** (8)：`mlock()`可以锁定的最大内存量。默认64KB。

7. **RLIMIT_NOFILE** (7)：进程可以打开的最大文件描述符数。默认1024（软限制），1048576（硬限制，由`fs.nr_open`控制）。

8. **RLIMIT_NPROC** (6)：用户可以创建的最大进程数。

9. **RLIMIT_STACK** (3)：栈大小上限。默认8MB。影响`execve()`时的初始栈大小。

10. **RLIMIT_MSGQUEUE** (12)：POSIX消息队列的最大字节数。

11. **RLIMIT_NICE** (13)：允许设置的最高nice值（20 - nice值）。

12. **RLIMIT_RTPRIO** (14)：允许设置的最高实时优先级。

**内核中的限制检查**：
```c
// 检查文件描述符限制
if (fd >= rlimit(RLIMIT_NOFILE))
    return -EMFILE;

// 检查内存限制
if (mm->total_vm > rlimit(RLIMIT_AS) >> PAGE_SHIFT)
    return -ENOMEM;

// 检查CPU时间
if (cputime_gt(utime + stime, rlimit(RLIMIT_CPU)))
    send_sig(SIGXCPU, current, 0);
```

**prlimit()**（系统调用302）：可以获取/设置其他进程的资源限制：
```c
prlimit(pid, RLIMIT_NOFILE, &new_limit, &old_limit);
```
需要`CAP_SYS_RESOURCE`或对目标进程有ptrace权限。

**/etc/security/limits.conf**：PAM模块`pam_limits.so`在用户登录时读取此配置文件，设置资源限制：
```
* soft nofile 65536
* hard nofile 65536
@developers soft memlock unlimited
```

**systemd集成**：systemd通过服务单元文件中的`LimitNOFILE=`、`LimitNPROC=`等指令设置服务的资源限制。

```c
#include <linux/mm.h>
#include <asm/pgtable.h>

/*
 * Identify which kernel virtual memory region a given
 * address belongs to on x86_64.
 */
static const char *identify_kernel_region(unsigned long addr)
{
    if (addr >= PAGE_OFFSET && addr < PAGE_OFFSET +
        (1UL << __VIRTUAL_MASK_SHIFT))
        return "Direct Map (linear mapping)";

    if (addr >= VMALLOC_START && addr < VMALLOC_END)
        return "vmalloc area";

    if (addr >= VMEMMAP_START && addr < VMEMMAP_START +
        VMEMMAP_SIZE)
        return "vmemmap (struct page array)";

    if (addr >= MODULES_VADDR && addr < MODULES_END)
        return "Module space";

    if (addr >= FIXADDR_START && addr < FIXADDR_TOP)
        return "Fixmap area";

    if (addr >= __START_KERNEL_map && addr <
        __START_KERNEL_map + KERNEL_IMAGE_SIZE)
        return "Kernel text (code + data)";

    if (addr >= CPU_ENTRY_AREA_BASE && addr <
        CPU_ENTRY_AREA_BASE + CPU_ENTRY_AREA_MAP_SIZE)
        return "CPU entry area";

    if (addr >= ESPFIX_BASE_ADDR)
        return "ESPFIX area (16-bit stack)";

    /* User space check */
    if (addr < TASK_SIZE_MAX)
        return "User space";

    return "Unknown/Invalid region";
}

/*
 * Print detailed information about a kernel address.
 */
static void inspect_kernel_addr(unsigned long addr)
{
    const char *region = identify_kernel_region(addr);
    pr_info("Address 0x%016lx: %s\n", addr, region);

    if (addr >= PAGE_OFFSET && addr < VMALLOC_START) {
        /* Direct map: can get physical address */
        phys_addr_t phys = __pa(addr);
        struct page *page = virt_to_page((void *)addr);
        pr_info("  Physical: 0x%llx, PFN: %lu\n",
                (u64)phys, phys >> PAGE_SHIFT);
        pr_info("  Page: refcount=%d, flags=0x%lx\n",
                page_ref_count(page), page->flags);
    } else if (addr >= VMALLOC_START && addr < VMALLOC_END) {
        /* vmalloc: get the backing pages */
        struct page *page = vmalloc_to_page((void *)addr);
        if (page)
            pr_info("  vmalloc backing page PFN: %lu\n",
                    page_to_pfn(page));
    }
}
```
此函数展示了x86_64内核虚拟地址空间的布局。每个区域服务于不同目的：Direct Map用于常规内核指针，vmalloc用于非连续分配，vmemmap存储struct page数组，Module space用于可加载模块。理解地址空间布局对内核调试（crash dump分析）和驱动开发至关重要。

When SMAP is enabled, the kernel cannot use normal memory access instructions to read or write user-space memory. The copy_to_user(), copy_from_user(), get_user(), and put_user() functions must temporarily disable SMAP before accessing user memory and re-enable it after. On x86, this is done with the STAC (Set AC flag) and CLAC (Clear AC flag) instructions, which toggle the EFLAGS.AC bit checked by SMAP. The stac() and clac() instructions are wrapped in uaccess_begin()/uaccess_end() macros. If a page fault occurs while SMAP is temporarily disabled, the fault handler knows it's a legitimate user access. However, if STAC/CLAC pairs are unbalanced (e.g., due to a bug), SMAP might remain disabled, creating a window for exploitation. The static_key mechanism optimizes the common case where SMAP is always on. The kernel's completion API for async operation synchronization:
```c
#include <linux/completion.h>

struct async_work {
    struct completion done;
    int result;
    void *data;
};

/* Callback invoked by hardware/DMA interrupt */
static void async_callback(void *arg)
{
    struct async_work *work = arg;
    work->result = read_status_register();
    complete(&work->done);  /* Wake up waiter */
}

/* Synchronous wrapper around async operation */
int do_async_operation_sync(void *data)
{
    struct async_work work;
    init_completion(&work.done);
    work.data = data;

    submit_async_operation(data, async_callback, &work);

    /* Wait with timeout */
    if (!wait_for_completion_timeout(&work.done,
                                      msecs_to_jiffies(5000)))
        return -ETIMEDOUT;

    return work.result;
}
```

IRQ affinity controls which CPUs can handle a given interrupt. This directly impacts locking design because it determines which CPUs might execute interrupt handlers.

**IRQ affinity mask**:
```c
struct irq_desc {
    struct cpumask *affinity;   /* CPUs that can handle this IRQ */
    /* ... */
};

/* Set IRQ to only CPU 0 */
echo 1 > /proc/irq/42/smp_affinity;

/* Set IRQ to CPUs 0-3 */
echo f > /proc/irq/42/smp_affinity;
```

**Locking implications**:
```c
/* If IRQ is affine to CPU 0 only: */
/* Process context on CPU 0 needs irqsave to prevent deadlock */
spin_lock_irqsave(&lock, flags);  /* Needed */

/* Process context on other CPUs: plain spin_lock is safe */
spin_lock(&lock);  /* IRQ won't fire on this CPU */
```

**Per-CPU IRQ optimization**:
```c
/* When IRQ is affine to a single CPU, you can use per-CPU data
 * instead of locks for the ISR's shared data */
static DEFINE_PER_CPU(struct isr_data, isr_state);

irqreturn_t handler(int irq, void *data) {
    /* Only runs on one CPU — no lock needed for per-CPU data */
    struct isr_data *s = this_cpu_ptr(&isr_state);
    s->count++;
    return IRQ_HANDLED;
}
```

**Multi-queue NIC with per-queue affinity**:
```c
/* Modern NICs have one IRQ per RX queue, each affine to one CPU */
/* Each CPU processes its own queue — no cross-CPU locking needed */
struct rx_queue {
    struct napi_struct napi;
    /* Per-queue data — no lock needed when affine to single CPU */
};
```

IRQ affinity is a powerful tool for reducing lock contention by partitioning interrupt handling across CPUs.

IA32_SPEC_CTRL (MSR 0x48) controls speculative execution mitigations: IBRS (Indirect Branch Restricted Speculation, bit 0), STIBP (Single Thread Indirect Branch Predictors, bit 1), SSBD (Speculative Store Bypass Disable, bit 2). Linux sets these based on CPU vulnerability and configuration. The 'spec_store_bypass_disable=' and 'spectre_v2=' boot parameters control settings. Updated via x86_spec_ctrl_set(). Example of using wait_event for blocking I/O completion:
```c
struct my_request {
    struct list_head list;
    wait_queue_head_t wait;
    int status;
    bool completed;
    void *data;
};

/* Submit request and wait */
int submit_and_wait(struct my_device *dev, void *data)
{
    struct my_request req = {
        .data = data,
        .completed = false,
        .status = 0,
    };
    init_waitqueue_head(&req.wait);

    spin_lock(&dev->lock);
    list_add_tail(&req.list, &dev->pending);
    spin_unlock(&dev->lock);

    /* Notify hardware there's work to do */
    writel(1, dev->base + DOORBELL_REG);

    /* Block until completion or timeout */
    wait_event_timeout(req.wait,
                       READ_ONCE(req.completed),
                       HZ * 10);

    if (!req.completed) {
        spin_lock(&dev->lock);
        list_del(&req.list);
        spin_unlock(&dev->lock);
        return -ETIMEDOUT;
    }
    return req.status;
}

/* Called from interrupt handler */
static irqreturn_t my_irq_handler(int irq, void *dev_id)
{
    struct my_device *dev = dev_id;
    struct my_request *req;

    req = get_completed_request(dev);
    if (!req)
        return IRQ_NONE;

    req->status = readl(dev->base + STATUS_REG);
    WRITE_ONCE(req->completed, true);
    wake_up(&req->wait);
    return IRQ_HANDLED;
}
```

Deadlock prevention in the Linux kernel relies on several strategies targeting the Coffman conditions, primarily circular wait through lock ordering.

**Strategy 1: Global Lock Ordering** — Define a total ordering on all locks and always acquire them in the same order.
```c
void lock_two(struct mutex *a, struct mutex *b) {
    if (a < b) { mutex_lock(a); mutex_lock(b); }
    else if (a > b) { mutex_lock(b); mutex_lock(a); }
}
```

**Strategy 2: Lock Hierarchy** — Assign each lock a level. Always acquire lower-numbered locks first. The kernel's lockdep enforces this.

**Strategy 3: Try-Lock and Back-Off**:
```c
int try_lock_all(struct mutex *locks[], int n) {
    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (!mutex_trylock(locks[i])) {
            while (--i >= 0) mutex_unlock(locks[i]);
            return -EDEADLK;
        }
    }
    return 0;
}
```

**Strategy 4: Lock Splitting** — Replace one big lock with multiple fine-grained locks.

**Strategy 5: Avoid Nested Locking** — Release-lock-then-reacquire patterns, per-CPU data, RCU, lock-free algorithms.

**Strategy 6: Preemption-based (rt_mutex)** — Priority inheritance prevents priority inversion.

**Kernel lockdep integration**: CONFIG_PROVE_LOCKING dynamically validates lock ordering at runtime, reporting potential deadlocks even before they occur.

The golden rule: Design your locking scheme so that lock ordering is a documented invariant. If lockdep complains, fix the design.

以下bpftrace脚本追踪块设备I/O请求的延迟分布，生成直方图：

```bash
# 追踪所有块设备I/O延迟
bpftrace -e '
tracepoint:block:block_rq_issue {
    @start[args->dev, args->sector] = nsecs;
}

tracepoint:block:block_rq_complete
/@start[args->dev, args->sector]/
{
    $lat = nsecs - @start[args->dev, args->sector];
    @latency = hist($lat);
    @iop = count();
    delete(@start[args->dev, args->sector]);
}

interval:s:5 {
    print(@latency);
    print(@iop);
    clear(@latency);
    clear(@iop);
}
'
```

更详细的版本，区分读写和按设备统计：
```bash
bpftrace -e '
tracepoint:block:block_rq_issue {
    @start[args->dev, args->sector] = nsecs;
    @rw[args->dev, args->sector] = args->rwbs[0];
}

tracepoint:block:block_rq_complete
/@start[args->dev, args->sector]/
{
    $lat = nsecs - @start[args->dev, args->sector];
    $rw = @rw[args->dev, args->sector];
    @read_lat[$rw == (int8_t)'R' ? "read" : "write"] = hist($lat);
    @dev_lat[args->dev] = hist($lat);
    delete(@start[args->dev, args->sector]);
    delete(@rw[args->dev, args->sector]);
}
'
```

输出直方图以纳秒为单位，可以通过除以1000转换为微秒。关注尾部延迟（p99、p999）而非平均值。

The `SYSCALL_DEFINE` family of macros is the standardized mechanism the Linux kernel uses to define system call handler functions. These macros provide type safety, generate proper function signatures, and insert necessary metadata for tracing and auditing.

**Macro Hierarchy**: The kernel provides `SYSCALL_DEFINE0` through `SYSCALL_DEFINE6`, where the number indicates the count of parameters (the kernel limits syscalls to a maximum of 6 arguments on most architectures):

```c
// 0 arguments
SYSCALL_DEFINE0(getpid) { return task_tgid_vnr(current); }

// 3 arguments
SYSCALL_DEFINE3(read, int, fd, char __user *, buf, size_t, count) {
    return ksys_read(fd, buf, count);
}
```

**Expansion Details**: `SYSCALL_DEFINE3(read, int, fd, char __user *, buf, size_t, count)` expands roughly to:

```c
// The actual handler with typed parameters
static long __se_sys_read(int fd, char __user *buf, size_t count);

// The wrapper that extracts args from pt_regs (architecture entry)
long __x64_sys_read(const struct pt_regs *regs) {
    return __se_sys_read(
        (int)regs->di,
        (char __user *)regs->si,
        (size_t)regs->dx
    );
}

// Sign-extension wrapper for 32-bit compat safety
static long __se_sys_read(int fd, char __user *buf, size_t count) {
    return __do_sys_read(fd, buf, count);
}

// The actual implementation body
static inline long __do_sys_read(int fd, char __user *buf, size_t count) {
    // ... implementation
}
```

The three layers serve distinct purposes:
1. `__x64_sys_read`: The architecture-specific entry point matching the `sys_call_table` signature `long (*)(const struct pt_regs *)`
2. `__se_sys_read`: The sign-extension wrapper ensures arguments from 32-bit user-space are properly sign-extended to 64-bit kernel `long` types (via `SYSCALL_DEFINEx`'s `__SC_LONG` and `__SC_CAST` macros)
3. `__do_sys_read`: The actual implementation with properly typed parameters

**Tracing Integration**: The macros also integrate with the kernel's tracing infrastructure. When `CONFIG_FTRACE_SYSCALLS` is enabled, each syscall gets associated `trace_event` structures:
```c
static struct syscall_metadata __syscall_meta_##sname = {
    .name = "sys_##sname",
    .syscall_nr = -1,  // Filled at boot
    .nb_args = nb,     // Number of arguments
    .types = types_##sname,
    .args = args_##sname,
};
```
This enables ftrace to trace all syscalls with argument printing via `/sys/kernel/debug/tracing/events/syscalls/`.

**The __user Annotation**: The `__user` annotation on pointer parameters (like `char __user *buf`) is a sparse static analysis marker. It indicates the pointer references user-space memory and must be accessed via `copy_from_user()`/`copy_to_user()` or `get_user()`/`put_user()`, never directly dereferenced in kernel code.

**Common Pattern**: Many syscall handlers in modern kernels delegate to `ksys_*` internal functions:
```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE3(read, int, fd, char __user *, buf, size_t, count) {
    return ksys_read(fd, buf, count);
}
```
This pattern separates the syscall interface from the kernel-internal API, allowing other kernel subsystems to call `ksys_read()` directly without going through the syscall machinery.

Process groups and sessions are hierarchical organizations of processes used for job control and signal delivery in Unix/Linux systems.

**Data Structures**:
```c
struct pid {
    unsigned int level;      // Namespace nesting level
    struct hlist_head tasks[PIDTYPE_MAX];  // Task lists per type
    struct upid numbers[];   // PID numbers per namespace
};

// PID types
enum pid_type {
    PIDTYPE_PID,      // Process ID
    PIDTYPE_TGID,     // Thread group ID
    PIDTYPE_PGID,     // Process group ID
    PIDTYPE_SID,      // Session ID
    PIDTYPE_MAX
};
```

**Process Group**: A collection of processes sharing the same PGID. Created by `setpgid()` (syscall 109):
```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE2(setpgid, pid_t, pid, pid_t, pgid) {
    struct task_struct *p;
    struct pid *pgrp;

    p = find_task_by_vpid(pid ? pid : task_pid_vnr(current));
    pgrp = pgid ? find_vpid(pgid) : task_pgrp(p);

    // Move process to the specified group
    change_pid(p, PIDTYPE_PGID, pgrp);
}
```

**Session**: A collection of process groups. Created by `setsid()` (syscall 112):
```c
SYSCALL_DEFINE0(setsid) {
    // Create new session with current process as leader
    struct pid *sid = task_pid(current);  // SID = PID of session leader
    set_special_pids(sid);
    // Process becomes session leader and process group leader
    // Detaches from controlling terminal
}
```

**Signal Delivery to Groups**: `kill(-pgid, sig)` sends signal to all processes in group `pgid`:
```c
// kernel/signal.c
static int kill_pgrp_info(int sig, struct kernel_siginfo *info, struct pid *pid) {
    // Iterate all processes in the process group
    do_each_pid_task(pid, PIDTYPE_PGID, p) {
        send_signal(sig, info, p);
    } while_each_pid_task(pid, PIDTYPE_PGID, p);
}
```

**Job Control**: The terminal driver uses process groups for foreground/background management:
- Foreground process group receives SIGINT (Ctrl+C), SIGTSTP (Ctrl+Z)
- Background processes writing to terminal receive SIGTTOU
- `tcsetpgrp()` sets the foreground process group

**Controlling Terminal**: Each session can have at most one controlling terminal (`/dev/tty`). The terminal's `tty->session` field tracks which session owns it.

